arts.ttl: Cheltenham Town v Bromley RECAP: Robins held by 10-man Ravens
arts.sum: Cheltenham Town: Day; Payne (Jude-Boyd 68), Bennett, Stubbs, Bradbury; Young, Kinsella (Taylor 87); Thomas (Bakare 68), Colwill (Pett 68), Archer; Miller (Bowman 81). Cheltenham Town had to settle for a point against 10-man Bromley, despite another goal for in-form Ethon Archer.

arts.ttl: Omar Sowunmi earns 10-man Bromley a point at Cheltenham
arts.sum: Carl Jenkinson was sent off midway through the first half.

arts.ttl: Senior duo setting example, belief in his players and praise for EFL Trophy - Cheltenham Town boss Michael Flynn after Reading win
arts.sum: It's important, it's more finances for the football club, it keeps the confidence going, but in a competition which is billed for youngsters, the best two players on the pitch were Joe Day and Tom Pett. I know a lot of the youngsters at Reading have been involved in the first team, regularly, but they have some outstanding youngsters, who play good football.
